college fees.

Currently, I am living in a Buddhist area with only old people, it is very sad seeing them having to reduce their food to only one meal a day to pay for their childrens education. Many children in Sri Lanka do no have anything to eat, they have no shoes, it is just very sad, and I know this because I grew up the same child, even now I remember being poor before my parents became successful now. I pray even just 1% of this money I raise goes to children.

I have great faith that this world is filled with kind-hearted and loving people. All of you have shown support for me and my family. I hope you can continue by helping the needy with all you have. I am asking you to spend a little or a lot however this small contribution can be so beneficial what could any of us lose? You could even take a friend and donate your way to a brighter day.

I truly appreciate every contribution given to me, please take time to read this and consider helping me on my way.

Kayal
